{"lemma":"حَيّ","slug":"حَيّ","root":"ح.#.#","root_slug":"ح-_-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-_-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَيّ","root":"حيي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":24},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":8,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9669","n9670","n9671"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"alternative form of حَيِيَ (ḥayiya, “to live”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to experience, to witness"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"alive"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"lively, animated, energetic, active"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"organism, living being"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tribe"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"neighbourhood, district (of a city), quarter (of a city)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"block of apartments"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"come! hurry up!","tags":["defective"],"examples":[{"text":"حَيَّ عَلَى ٱلصَّلَاةِ","english":"Come to prayer!"},{"text":"حَيَّ عَلَى الْفَلَاحِ","english":"hurry up and work!"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of حَيَاء (ḥayāʔ)","tags":["form-of","plural"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَوَى (ḥawā) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew חי (khay), Ge'ez ሐይወ (ḥäywä).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/ħajj/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9669","headword_ar":"حَىَّ","root":"HY: or HY and Hyw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a verbal noun, (S, M, Mgh, TA,) and therefore immediately followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, TA,) used as an imperative [addressed to a single person, male or female, and to more than one]; (S;) used in calling, or summoning, or inviting, and urging; (Lth, T, TA;) and having no verb derived from it [alone, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayoEala","text_ar":"حَيْعَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a","text_ar":"حَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"together]; (Lth, T, Msb, TA;) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh, Msb, K, TA, &c.:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"come quickly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hasten."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a EalaY AlS~alaAhN","text_ar":"حَىَّ عَلَى الصَّلَاهٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(in the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a*aAn","text_ar":"اَذَان"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come to prayer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IKt, S, M, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"come ye to prayer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"come ye quickly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hasten ye."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a EalaY AlfalaAHo","text_ar":"حَىَّ عَلَى الفَلَاحْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the same: see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"flH","text_ar":"فلح"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a EalaY AlgadaA='i","text_ar":"حَىَّ عَلَى الغَدَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come to the morning-meal"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY AlEa$aA='i","text_ar":"على العَشَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the evening-meal"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY Alv~ariydi","text_ar":"على الثَّرِيدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the crumbled bread moistened with broth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY Alxayori","text_ar":"على الخَيْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to good, good fortune, prosperity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (Lth, T, TA.) The saying of Ibn-Ahmar,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"HaY~a AlHumuwla faA_in~a Alr~akoba qado *ahabaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Keep thou to the loads"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the riders upon the camels have gone"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  In the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a hala","text_ar":"حَىَّ هَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a halFA","text_ar":"حَىَّ هَلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalaY","text_ar":"عَلَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY ka*aA","text_ar":"اـِلَى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a halaA","text_ar":"حَىَّ هَلَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which last is used in a case of pausation, but is bad in other cases, (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hl","text_ar":"هل"},{"kind":"text","text":",) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a halo","text_ar":"حَىَّ هَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~ahol","text_ar":"حَيَّهْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", [so in the copies of the K,] with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent, (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HY~ hln","text_ar":"حىّ هلن"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a halano","text_ar":"حَىَّ هَلَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a halFA","text_ar":"حَىَّ هَلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", or perhaps a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a halaka","text_ar":"حَىَّ هَلَكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (TA,) [the most common rendering of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a hala","text_ar":"حَىَّ هَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. is like that of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a","text_ar":"حَىَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, namely,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HY~","text_ar":"حىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hasten thou;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hl","text_ar":"هل"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hlA","text_ar":"هلا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"come to it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reach it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so that the meaning is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hasten thou: come to such a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HY~","text_ar":"حىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"come;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hl","text_ar":"هل"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hlA","text_ar":"هلا"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaviyvFA","text_ar":"حَثِيثًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"), or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be thou quick;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so that the meaning is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"come quickly to such a thing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hl","text_ar":"هل"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hlA","text_ar":"هلا"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be thou quiet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the meaning is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asoriEo Einoda *ikorihi waA@sokuno Hat~aY yanoqaDiYa","text_ar":"اَسْرِعْ عِنْدَ ذِكْرِهِ وَا@سْكُنْ حَتَّى يَنْقَضِىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Speed thou at the mention thereof, and be quiet until it is finished"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) Accord. to Abu-lKhattáb, the Arabs used to say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a hala AlS~alaApa","text_ar":"حَىَّ هَلَ الصَّلَاةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Come thou to prayer."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a halo bifulaAnK","text_ar":"حَىَّ هَلْ بِفُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, and so in the CK,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a halFA bflAn","text_ar":"حَىَّ هَلًا بفلان"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, and so in MS. copies of the K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a hala bflAn","text_ar":"حَىَّ هَلَ بفلان"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hasten thou with such a one:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keep thou to such a one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"call him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":681},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_i*aA *ukira AlS~aAliHuwna fiHaY~a hala biEumara","text_ar":"اـِذَا ذُكِرَ الصَّالِحُونَ فِحَىَّ هَلَ بِعُمَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hl","text_ar":"هل"},{"kind":"text","text":",) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faHay~ahalFA biEumara","text_ar":"فَحَيَّهَلًا بِعُمَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"When the good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"righteous, are mentioned, then"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"keep thou to 'Omar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"call 'Omar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S ubi suprà, and TA,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"begin with him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"be quick in mentioning him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) for he is of such. (S ubi suprà.) Accord. to some of the grammarians, (TA,) when you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~a halFA","text_ar":"حَىَّ هَلًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", with tenween, it is as though you said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hav~FA","text_ar":"حَثًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and without tenween, it is as though you said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHav~a","text_ar":"الحَثَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the tenween being made a sign of indeterminateness; and the omission of it, a sign of determinateness: and so it is in all compounds of this kind. (K.) [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hl","text_ar":"هل"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Mgh","TA","IKt","Msb","K","IAar"]},{"entry_id":"n9670","headword_ar":"حَىٌّ","root":"HY: or HY and Hyw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Living, having life, alive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"may~itN","text_ar":"مَيِّتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mayotN","text_ar":"مَيْتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Mgh, * Msb, * K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayawaAnN","text_ar":"حَيَوَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~N","text_ar":"حَىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having animal life"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IB:) dim. of the former ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuyaY~N","text_ar":"حُيَىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^HoyaA='N","text_ar":"احْيَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, K.) When you say of a person,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa biHaY~K","text_ar":"لَيْسَ بِحَىٍّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", you mean that he is dead: (Lh:) but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohaA","text_ar":"مِنْهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Duriba DarobapF layosa biHaAYK","text_ar":"ضُرِبَ ضَرْبَةً لَيْسَ بِحَاىٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, K,) [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Daraba","text_ar":"ضَرَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and] in [some of] the copies of the K, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biHaA='K","text_ar":"بِحَا=ءٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was struck a blow"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in consequence of which he will not live:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, K: *) like as the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA taA^okulo ka*aA faA_in~aka maAriDN","text_ar":"لَا تَاْكُلْ كَذَا فَاـِنَّكَ مَارِضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means Thou wilt be sick if thou eat such a thing. (Lh, K.) Accord. to ISh, one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ataAnaA HaY~u fulaAnK","text_ar":"اَتَانَا حَىُّ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one came to us in his life"},{"kind":"text","text":"[-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"samiEotu HaY~a fulaAnK yaquwlu ka*aA","text_ar":"سَمِعْتُ حَىَّ فُلَانٍ يَقُولُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I heard such a one say thus in his life"},{"kind":"text","text":"[-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"time"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) [or the former may mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one himself came to us:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I heard such a one himself say thus:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HY","text_ar":"حى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~","text_ar":"حَىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a prefixed noun] is sometimes redundant, like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=l","text_ar":"ا=ل"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw","text_ar":"ذُو"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ham p. 308:) [and] IB says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~u fulaAnK","text_ar":"حَىُّ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one himself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And they say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aholika","text_ar":"اَهْلِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kayofa A^anota waHay~apu","text_ar":"كَيْفَ اَنْتَ وَحَيَّةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"How art thou, and those remaining alive of thy family?"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  Applied to God,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Deathless."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Possessing the faculty of growth, as an animal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a plant:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib:) and, applied to a plant,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fresh, juicy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"succulent, and growing tall."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sensitively alive;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing the faculty of sensation."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib.) ―         -b5-  (assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Intellectually alive;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"possessing the faculty of intellect."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib.) [Hence,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A Muslim;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"may~itN","text_ar":"مَيِّتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means an unbeliever. (TA.) ―         -b6-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lively,"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from grief"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sorrow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib.) ―         -b7-  (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whole, sound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unbroken."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SA^b","text_ar":"صاب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^araDN Hay~apN","text_ar":"اَرَضٌ حَيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fruitful land;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"land abounding with herbage;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArD mayotapN","text_ar":"ارض مَيْتَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means unfruitful land. (TA.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~amosu Hay~apN","text_ar":"الشَّمْسُ حَيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sun is,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was, of a clear colour, unaltered by approaching the place of setting;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as though its setting were regarded as death: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"still bright and white:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"still hot and powerful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but the former of these two meanings is the more probable. (Mgh.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naArN Hay~apN","text_ar":"نَارٌ حَيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A live,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burning, fire."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AHn.) ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqN HaY~N","text_ar":"طَرِيقٌ حَىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An apparent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a distinct, road"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoyaA='N","text_ar":"اَحْيَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hay~apN","text_ar":"حَيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", first sentence.       -A3-  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tribe"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of the Arabs: (S:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"children,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"descendants, of one father"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ancestor, whether many or few:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aEob","text_ar":"شَعْب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comprising"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaAy^il","text_ar":"قَبَايِل"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Az, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiylap","text_ar":"قَبِيلَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Arabs: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baTon","text_ar":"بَطْن"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buTuwn","text_ar":"بُطُون"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Arabs: (K, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoyaA='N","text_ar":"اَحْيَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K.)       -A4-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vulva,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"external portion of the organs of generation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a woman. (Az, K. See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayaA='N","text_ar":"حَيَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~N","text_ar":"حَىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also said to be a pl.) Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEafu AlHaY~i","text_ar":"سَعَفُ الحَىِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied by an Arab of the desert to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The paraphernalia of a bride."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA.)       -A5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAHaY~a Eanohu","text_ar":"لَاحَىَّ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laAmanoEa minohu","text_ar":"لَامَنْعَ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Ks, K, *) i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is no forbiddance of him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nothing is forbidden him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr.)       -A6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yaEorifu","text_ar":"لَا يَعْرِفُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaY~a mina All~aY~i","text_ar":"الحَىَّ مِنَ اللَّىِّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He knows not,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"will not know, what is true from what is false;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K, Har p. 236;) and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaw~a mn All~aw~i","text_ar":"الحَوَّ من اللَّوِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hawiy~ap","text_ar":"حَوِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"winding gut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the twisting of the rope:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overt speech from covert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the living from the dead:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the act of turning round,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"winding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaAhu","text_ar":"حَوَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HwY","text_ar":"حوى"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of which"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~N","text_ar":"حَىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an inf. n.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the act of twisting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har ubi suprà.)       -A7-  The act of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collecting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [But in this and some other senses it is an inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaY","text_ar":"حَوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HwY","text_ar":"حوى"},{"kind":"text","text":".])       -A8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoyaA='N","text_ar":"اَحْيَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaA='N","text_ar":"حَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HwA^","text_ar":"حوا"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["IB","Msb","Lh","K","TA","S","Az"]},{"entry_id":"n9671","headword_ar":"حِىٌّ","root":"HY: or HY and Hyw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayaApN","text_ar":"حَيَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which it is said to be a syn.: and of which it is also said to be a pl.:       -A2-  and see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HayaA='N","text_ar":"حَيَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", of which, also, it is said to be a pl."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}